                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d762">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Lord <persName type="from">Pauncefote</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">British Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-04-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 18, 1900</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 111.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to your personal note of March 16,
                    and your note, No. 1753, of April 6, I have the honor, by direction of Her
                    Majesty’s principal secretary of state for foreign affairs, to convey to your
                    Government the thanks of Her Majesty’s Government for the success which has
                    attended the efforts of the United States consul on behalf of the British
                    prisoners of war at Pretoria.</p>
                <p>As regards the treatment of Boer prisoners by British authorities, I am to inform
                    you that telegrams, books, clothing, and luxuries are freely transmitted to them
                    after inspection; that small amounts of money are given to them direct, while
                    larger amounts are handed to the commandant to issue in small sums, and that
                    clothing is issued at the public expense to prisoners who are in great need of
                    it.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Pauncefote.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
